au.aklein.metajava

Interface Element

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnnotationElement, ClassElement, FieldElement, MethodElement, ParameterElement

    public interface Element
    An element which is represented in a class file (either a ClassElement, a MethodElement, a FieldElement or an AnnotationElement

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Get the name of the element being represented. As this is based off the au.aklein.metajava.internal representation of the element's binary name, names are delimited by forward slashes (/) instead of periods as described in the JLS.
        Returns:
        A string containing the element's name

      • has

        boolean has(Element element)
        Check if the current element contains the specified element.
        Parameters:
        element - - The element to check.
        Returns:
        - True if the current element contains the specified element, otherwise false.

      • type

        ElementType type()
        Report the ElementType of the current element.
        Returns:
